  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prospective randomized study in cemented primary total knee arthroplasty. In one group the
      cement used was standard cement, without any antibiotics and in the other group the cement
      used was loaded with 0.5 g of erythromycin and 3 million units of colistin in 40 g of cement.
      In all cases intravenous antibiotics prophylaxis against infection was used. In both groups
      the cement was mechanically mixed in a vacuum. One deep drain tube was placed for 24 hours in
      all cases. The main variable was the presence of infection according to the Center of Disease
      Control criteria with a minimum of 12 months follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
